The paper deals with the task of image set classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Covariance Descriptors (CovDs) and Riemannian manifold metrics is a common approach in pattern recognition and machine learning, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the Nystrom method, which is a technique for approximating large matrices, and this falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper applies the proposed framework to three benchmark datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
